subject: p13475033
History: Leukocytosis. PA and lateral upright chest radiographs were reviewed in comparison to. Heart size and mediastinum are stable. No definitive focal consolidation is demonstrated. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. Focal narrowing of the mid trachea is noted and might potentially be related to prior intubation.
Impression: No definitive evidence of infectious process within the limitations of this study technique. If clinically warranted, correlation with chest CT might be considered.
